An Act
ENROLLED HOUSE
BILL NO. 1370 By: Boles, Stewart, Provenzano,
and Eaves of the House
and
Green of the Senate
An Act relating to the Motor Fuel Tax Code; repealing
68 O.S. 2021, Section 500.4A, which relates to
reduction in federal excise tax on gasoline or diesel
fuel; and declaring an emergency.
SUBJECT: Motor Fuel Tax Code
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. REPEALER 68 O.S. 2021, Section 500.4A, is
hereby repealed.
SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
be in full force from and after its passage and approval.

Passed the House of Representatives the 14th day of May, 2026.
Presiding Officer of the House
of Representatives
Passed the Senate the 14th day of May, 2026.
